The Americas
------------
[2] Chile (9th case/vaccination policy)
Date: 14 Jul 2015
Source: La Tercera [In Spanish, machine translation. edited Mod.CP]
http://www.latercera.com/noticia/nacional/2015/07/680-638791-9-ministerio-de-salud-confirma-noveno-caso-de-sarampionshtml


The Health Ministry today confirmed a 9th case of measles in the country. This [case] is a woman of 27 years who lives in the metropolitan area, which is linked to the 3rd person infected. The Health Ministry said that, like all confirmed cases that are directly related to the 3rd case, the woman was under surveillance and blocking [isolation?] measures were taken early. In addition, the Health Ministry reiterated that travelers who visit countries [where there ongoing measles cases?] have the recommended measles vaccination, especially:

- People born between 1971 and 1981, who have no history of the disease or have completed 2 doses of the vaccine after 12 months.
- Infants 6-11 months of age traveling to countries with cases.
- Children between 1-6 years have an administered dose, traveling to countries with cases.

To be vaccinated free of charge at public or private facilities requires a doctor's order or passage from his next trip, said the Ministry.

